txt.en: Bring the marsh-fly wings to Captain Agelmund
Captain Agelmund is at Feldburg, awaiting your return.\n\nYou should bring the wings you gathered to Captain Agelmund.
The Stinging Bog is home to a number of marsh-flies that carry upon them trophies -- insect-wings that are valuable to merchants and townsfolk.

'Ah! What have we here? I see that you collected several perfectly intact wings of marsh-flies from that horrible bog. These are actually quite valuable, for they have beauty for those with an eye for such things; the merchants can make much of them.\n\n'Few trappers are skilled enough to wrangle these wings from the flies without damaging them. A trophy well-earned!'
The Stinging Bog is home to a number of marsh-flies that carry upon them trophies -- insect-wings that are valuable to merchants and townsfolk.
Wings can be collected form marsh-flies that inhabit the Stinging Bog, on the far side of the road from Feldburg.\n\nYou should collect marsh-fly wings from the Stinging Bog's large pests.
